Description: Fragments of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Handle in very many small fragments. Rectangular stamp. Clay near fine light brown; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Common type, but probably from Naukratis. Petrie drew several in his diary. Name Imas.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0931)
